## Assistant

I adjusted the bottom bar so it sits higher, matching the previous status offset:

- Set `.bottom-bar` to `bottom: 12px` with standard padding.
- When installed as a PWA, it now moves up to `bottom: calc(env(safe-area-inset-bottom) + 10vh)` like the old status did.

Here are the updated rules:

```/Users/samuel-skean/Coding/speedometer/index.html#L62-78
            .bottom-bar {
                position: fixed;
                left: 0;
                bottom: 12px;
                width: 100%;
                display: grid;
                grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
                align-items: center;
                padding: 12px;
                box-sizing: border-box;
            }
            body.pwa-installed .bottom-bar {
                bottom: calc(env(safe-area-inset-bottom) + 10vh);
            }
```

That should give you the same comfortable vertical offset as before. If you want a slightly different lift on non-PWA browsers, we can make the 12px a variable or scale it with `clamp()` to account for varied densities.

